Official (late) happy anniversary post to @t_reynolds22. Wow, #Wyoming was the perfect escape for 🎶 “just the two of us. We can make it if we try, just the two of us, you and I…” 🎶 (come on all the oldies should know that tune). Marriage isn’t always blissful, but you can always find the beauty in between the hard rocks/times and stillness/peacefulness.

Thank you for making anywhere with you feel like home. #ILY

Because it’s #MedalMonday, or more like mindset everyday. Race day wrap-up for the 2022 endurance season with my favorite PR course @sandiegoholidayhalf marathon. Incredibly grateful to have finished with a “strava official” half-marathon time of 1:33:12 and 5th in age-group. Not to mention the best support crew (my family) cheering with my big head and being there when I needed them most! 

Aside from the shiny metal and pace PR blah, in all truthfulness, it’s your mindset that gets you to the start AND finish line. Leading up to this I did the long-runs every weekend, I put in the work, I did my workouts according to my coach’s program for me. But the past month+ I mentally haven’t been present for my workouts, and I barely made it to the start line. The days leading up to the race I knew if I were going to do it, I had to change my mindset and refocus on what I know I’ve been physically working so hard for and just get my mind right! Anyways long story long, DO NOT discredit mentally strengthening your ability to accomplish anything you put your mind too! I especially needed the mental strength for the last 5k push when my legs were just about ☠️. 

Huge thank you to the best coach Felipe @btathletes and my fellow teammates who physically and mentally push me to reach my highest potential 🙌🏼. It never gets easier, we just get better and #TrustTheProcess!!

#HalfMarathon #Mindset #RunningMotivation #OrangePower #BTathletes #Triathlon #MomOnTheRun #HardcoreFitnessSD #SanDiegoRunning #Tri #Guam

Walking into Monday like… 🎶this, this, this🎶

I know some will see/hear this song and immediately think “Wow, she must think she’s all that and a bag of chips (make it spicy)🤪”. But the truth is we live in such a world where especially on social media it’s ok to be complimented by others, but it’s not good to compliment ourselves and say “today I do look pretty, today I do feel good about myself”. As someone who has always struggled with self-image, loving myself (as much as I pour into loving others), and taking a compliment (without refuting it), I can appreciate when someone can confidently rock who they are! So my #motivation for anyone who sees this (even the dudes), is to give yourself permission to walk into today and tomorrow and then next with a “pretty girl” attitude with your shoulders back and head held high 🙃!

In light of @ironman70.3oceanside tomorrow and not being able to race (due to an injury) as initially planned, flashback to my 1st #Ironman703 and my 2nd ever triathlon! Straight fear-(ful/less)!! 

1.2 miles (58 degrees) ocean swim 🏊🏼‍♀️
56 miles bike 🚴🏻‍♀️
13.1 miles run 🏃🏻‍♀️

I never posted these pics hoping I’d find the right time and right words to express everything I experienced, and a year later here we are missing this race (mostly the process). This race wasn’t anything close to “as planned” - managing through a scary asthma attack during the cold AF ocean swim and seemingly hypothermia as I started the bike ride with uncontrollable teeth chattering. But if there’s a few words of advice from this amateur, is to ENJOY and embrace it all (smile it lessens the pain 🤪), be grateful for the ability to challenge yourself, your character, and placing yourself in a place where you can feel fear and get uncomfortable; something that many others aren’t willing to do. It’s more than a race, it’s a testament to the tenacity of your spirit and endurance. Be grateful to get to the start line because you’ve had to fight so hard to show up (and this race prep I fought really f*cking hard and went through some really tough moments), sacrificing family time, sleep, work, etc. This one day is not nearly as hard as the long weekends of training for the past months to get to the finish line. 

And lastly, whatever it is you’re doing, races or not, as the nerves and anxiousness amounts, remember on the other side of fear is the person you want to become! #TrustTheProcess

Always special thanks to my family/friends and #1 sherpa @t_reynolds22, the best coach @breakawaytraining who’s guided me into becoming the athlete I never imagined was possible, and to the best teammates @btathletes. Good luck to all those #IronmanOceanside703 racers!

Triathlon Thursday 🏊🏼‍♀️🚴🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️. 

Starting off the tri-season @sdtriseries Spring Sprint and bringing home a first place🥇for age-group. First time racing a Sprint distance and first time my family wasn’t there because the race went by way too fast! Coming back from an injury was a little nerve wrecking and knowing that the sprint distance was straight red zone speed, I knew I had to turn it up! Had an absolute blast with my @btathletes teammates and so thankful to do this suffer-fest with none other than them. To top it off, was cheerfully surprised by my #1 cheer squad with my big heads in hand curbside as I got home! 

For me, racing isn’t just about winning per se (of course I want to excel in my age-group and be competitive), but I consider a true win when I can improve in every sport - swim/bike/run. So here’s to the beginning of a great start to the season and can’t wait to work harder towards race PR’s. Let’s gooo!!!

My WHY… 

Finally decompressed and posting the professional pics from Ironman Santa Cruz 70.3 and WOW, What. A. Course!! #SantaCruz you are beautiful!! 

1.2 mile ocean swim 🏊🏼‍♀️
56 miles bike 🚴🏻‍♀️
13.1 miles run 🏃🏻‍♀️

Two weeks before the race I was having huge anxiety attacks thinking about the swim, a week before the race I wasn’t sure if I could even run 10 miles without stopping, and a day before the race I crashed and had deep open wounds that really made me wonder if I should go to urgent care vs. doing the dang race! I prayed SO hard through it all and I ended up at the start and finish line to realize my “WHY”. Because some day I want my kids to know that Mommy did hard things, she was consistent, she was determined, she was strong, and she was happy doing these “crazy” things 🤪… I also want people to know that when things go sideways, always have faith and #TrustInTheProcess.

No journey is how we ever plan or imagine and I truly am thankful for all the strength, endurance, love and support that God has gifted me to be capable of mentally and physically being here and doing it all 🙏🏼! Second personal best for a half-marathon, and I’ll gladly take it 🙌🏼!! 

Thank you to my coach Felipe @btathletes who puts so much energy and encouragement in me to reach my highest potential. And immense gratitude for @t_reynolds22 and my kids for being my support and Sherpa, I wouldn’t be doing this without my family by my side. Until next one 70.3…

@breakawaytraining #BTathletes #SantaCruz703 #Ironman #Triathlon #MomOnTheRun #HardcoreFitnessSD

Wrapping up #IMSantaCruz 70.3 and still reminiscing on it all. Every journey and story is different, but for me it’s a spiritual one. The long training days, left to my own thoughts I found myself praying A LOT, asking to give me the strength and endurance to get me through the tough days. If you’ve done endurance sports, you’ll know that a lot of the days it’s really a mind f*ck and all you have to remind yourself is that “what the mind believes, the body achieves”. Last pic is of 1 out of 2 wounds day before the race; a great reminder that when I asked God to make me strong, he showed me how strong I am and got me to the finish line to see my family. When faced with adversity and challenge, there is the pinnacle of if you’re strong enough to have a breakthrough. #TRIharder friends 👊🏼. #AnythingIsPossible 

#IM703 #Triathlon #BTathletes #HardcoreFitnessSD

Another adventure for our anniversary in #Hawaii, but a different kind of love story found in the deep blue 🌊🦈…

Falling in love with doing all things fearlessly has been my life goal as I’ve gotten older (even though we tend to fear more things as we age), you only live once right?! After having a scary near-drowning moment trying to surf in Nicu, to swearing I’d never swim in the open water without a wetsuit, let alone the fear of sharks and sea animals in the ocean… this experience would have been a hard pass for me. But here we are, 3 miles off the #NorthShore, free diving searching to swim with sharks in their territory. Huge milestone moment that I never want to forget. Incredible experience through @oneoceandiving, thank you for making it so special. It really is a romantic time down in the deep blue @t_reynolds22 💙! 

BTW #freediving without a weight belt, so hard, also so much respect for free diving in general! #Sharks get such a bad rep mostly because people aren’t well educated, but they are so beautiful and peaceful. Highly recommend this once in a lifetime experience.

Instead of taking formal #Hawaii anniversary pics, we chose this instead 📸🦈... 3 miles off shore, dumped into a sea of sharks, til death do us part (glad you didn’t die tho) @t_reynolds22 👰🏻‍♀️🤵🏻‍♂️. Pretty romantic down in the deep blue. Thankful for a partner like you and going along with my crazy adventures! Incredible footage @oneoceandiving 🌊.
